The paper deals with algorithms for graph connectivity problems, which are typically studied in the area of data structures (cs.DS) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The focus on read-write asymmetry and write-efficient algorithms suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the area of computational complexity (cs.CC) and systems and control (cs.SI). Finally, the use of parallel algorithms and the analysis of large graphs suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the area of data mining (cs.DM).
